  "text": "To implement an InventoryConsumer following Kafka codebase patterns, the agent should reference these key files in sg-evals/kafka--0753c489: (1) ConsumerConfig.java defines all configuration constant fields including BOOTSTRAP_SERVERS_CONFIG, GROUP_ID_CONFIG, KEY_DESERIALIZER_CLASS_CONFIG, VALUE_DESERIALIZER_CLASS_CONFIG, ENABLE_AUTO_COMMIT_CONFIG, and AUTO_OFFSET_RESET_CONFIG. (2) KafkaConsumer.java is the main consumer implementation with poll(Duration) and commitSync() methods, and its Javadoc (lines 440-476) shows the canonical WakeupException handling pattern using AtomicBoolean closed flag, try/catch WakeupException, and consumer.close() in finally block. (3) Consumer.java is the interface defining commitSync() and poll(Duration) contracts. (4) WakeupException.java defines the exception used to preempt blocking poll() for clean shutdown via consumer.wakeup(). (5) examples/Consumer.java is the canonical example showing ConsumerConfig constant usage for all properties, poll(Duration.ofSeconds(1)) call, and commitSync() on offset reset. (6) VerifiableConsumer.java demonstrates commitSync with explicit WakeupException handling in a real consumer loop with poll(Duration) and consumer.close() in finally.",
